A '''non-denominational''' person or organization is not restricted to any particular or specific [[religious denomination]].
==Overview== The term has been used in the context of various faiths including [[Jainism]],<ref>Jainism in a global perspective: - Page 115, Sāgaramala Jaina, Shriprakash Pandey, Pārśvanātha Vidyāpīṭha - 1998</ref> [[Baha'i Faith]],<ref>Earth Versus the Science-fiction Filmmakers - Page 70, Tom Weaver - 2005</ref> [[Zoroastrianism]],<ref>Zoroastrianism: An Introduction - Page 227, Jenny Rose - 2011</ref> [[Unitarian Universalism]],<ref>{{cite book|last1=Resourcewomen|title=Religious Funding Resource Guide|date=2000|page=439}}</ref> [[paganism]],<ref>{{cite book|last1=Mammone|first1=Andrea|title=Varieties of Right-Wing Extremism in Europe|date=2013}}</ref> [[Christianity]],<ref>Models for Christian Higher Education, Richard Thomas Hughes, William B. Adrian - 1997, p 403</ref> [[Islam]],<ref name="Pollack">{{cite book|last1=Pollack|first1=Kenneth|title=Unthinkable: Iran, the Bomb, and American Strategy |date=2014 |page=29 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jQGZBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA29 |quote=Although many Iranian hardliners are Shi'a chauvinists, Khomeini's ideology saw the revolution as pan-Islamist, and therefore embracing Sunni, Shi'a, Sufi, and other, more '''nondenominational Muslims'''}}</ref> [[Judaism]],<ref>Continuity and Change, Steven T. Katz, Steven Bayme - 2012, p 268</ref> [[Hinduism]],<ref>Personality Of Adolescent Students - Page 42, D.B. Rao - 2008</ref> [[Buddhism]]<ref>The Buddhist Experience in America - Page 147, Diane Morgan - 2004</ref> and [[Wicca]].<ref>Wiccan Warrior: Walking a Spiritual Path in a Sometimes Hostile World - Page 173, Kerr Cuhulain - 2000</ref> It stands in contrast with a [[religious denomination]]. Religionists of a non-denominational persuasion tend to be more open-minded in the views on various religious matters and rulings. Some converts towards non-denominational strains of thought have been influenced by disputes over traditional teachings in the previous institutions they attended.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Boyd|first1=Gloria|title=African American Religious Experiences|date=2010|page=6}}</ref> Nondenominationalism has also been used as a tool for introducing neutrality into a public square when the local populace are derived from a wide-ranging set of religious beliefs.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Pope|first1=Robert|title=T&T Clark Companion to Nonconformity|date=2013|page=320}}</ref>
